    "collapsible_content_JN3rhi": {
      "type": "collapsible-content",
      "blocks": {
        "collapsible_row_UjR4JN": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How does Reviv work differently from CPAP machines for sleep apnea?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>While CPAP machines force air into your airways to keep them open during sleep, I view that Reviv addresses the root structural issues.</p><p>And gradually corrects the structural issues that cause airway collapse in the first place.  </p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_tUj3HX": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How long does it take to see improvements in sleep apnea with Reviv?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>I have seen some folks report improvements in their sleep in the first 1-2 months. </p><p>But it can take longer.</p><p>And note that this is based on what I have seen in folks doing Reviv and we are not claiming that a mouthguard will always fix sleep apnea.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_6bErhk": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Is it difficult to wear Reviv?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Many users can find the initial weeks difficult with some soreness of teeth and gums.</p><p>I view that the soft tissue is stretching and that with time it gets easier to sleep with the mouthguard.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_jEbzGk": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Can I wear my CPAP with Reviv?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Yes a number of folks have done this and it doesn't seem to be an issues.</p><p>I believe that eventually things should open sufficiently that it could be possible to stop the use of the CPAP.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "collapsible_row_UjR4JN",
